This is usually measured through established research methodologies under the term “usability testing,” which includes success rates and customer satisfaction. While UX encompasses designing the overall experience of a product, usability focuses on the mechanics of making sure products work as well as possible for the user.

Fellows are hired as full-time federal employees at a GS-15 level, Step 1, serving a 1-2 year term in Washington, D.C.
